## Interpretation

Cycle 2 produced a genuine buy-hold-relative development improvement: the best slow-trend plus fold-local low-volatility overlay beat always-long net, improved drawdown, improved funding-aware score, and passed the default causality gate budget. The weakness is cost robustness: cost3x and cost5x are negative because turnover is much higher than passive exposure.

The next cycle should search for a low-turnover regime overlay that keeps the drawdown and funding-aware gains while preserving cost survival. The cost-surviving funding and drawdown filters are weaker on raw net but are useful controls.

